<section>
    <center class="ml-4">
        <h1 style=" font-size:30px; font-weight:600; margin-left: -500px; margin:15px;">Fun Facts on Plant Care</h1>
        
    </center>
    <div class="plant-care">
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>1. Watering</h3>
            <p>Determine the specific watering needs of each plant. Consider factors like species, soil moisture, climate, and season. Avoid overwatering or underwatering, and ensure proper drainage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>2. Light</h3>
            <p>Provide adequate light based on the plant's requirements. Some need direct sunlight, while others thrive in shade or indirect light. Monitor and adjust light exposure accordingly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>3. Soil and Potting</h3>
            <p>Choose appropriate soil for the plant species. Ensure good drainage and use pots with suitable sizes. Repot when necessary to accommodate growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>4. Fertilizing</h3>
            <p>Use fertilizers to provide essential nutrients. Follow instructions and avoid over-fertilizing, as it can harm plants. Apply fertilizer during the growing season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>5. Pruning and Trimming</h3>
            <p>Regularly prune dead or damaged parts to encourage healthy growth. Maintain the plant's shape and size through trimming and remove wilted flowers to encourage new blooms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>6. Pest and Disease Control</h3>
            <p>Monitor plants for pests and diseases. Use natural remedies or appropriate treatments to control pests and address diseases promptly to prevent spreading.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>7. Temperature and Humidity</h3>
            <p>Understand the temperature and humidity needs of your plants. Keep them in suitable environments and protect them from extreme conditions or sudden temperature changes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="care-point">
            <h3>8. Monitoring and Care Routine</h3>
            <p>Regularly observe your plants for signs of issues. Establish a care routine including watering schedules, checking for pests, and providing necessary care based on individual plant needs.</p>
        </div>
    </div>


</section>





